Add Windows (winsock2) portability layer to microsocks.

Upstream microsocks is POSIX-only. Zig cc's x86_64-windows-gnu target
(mingw-w64 headers) lacks <sys/socket.h>, <netinet/in.h>, <arpa/inet.h>,
<poll.h>, and SIGPIPE. This patch ifdef-guards all POSIX-specific
includes, swaps poll() for WSAPoll(), read()/write() on sockets for
recv()/send(), close() for closesocket(), provides dprintf/usleep
shims (mingw-w64 doesn't expose them by default), and drops SIGPIPE
handling on Windows. Linux/BSD/macOS builds are unaffected.

